version: 1
display_name: VCFJ-9X-000008 - The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations HCX Apache HTTP service must initiate session logging upon start up.
global_description: |-
  An attacker can compromise a web server during the startup process. If logging is not initiated until all the web server processes are started, key information may be missed and not be available during a forensic investigation. To ensure all logable events are captured, the web server must begin logging once the first web server process is initiated.
osfinger:
  - VMware Photon OS-5
refs:
  disa_stig:
    - VCFJ-9X-000008
  srg:
    - SRG-APP-000092-WSR-000055
  cci:
    - CCI-001464
    - CCI-001851
  nist:
    - AU-14 (1)
    - AU-4 (1)
benchmark_id:
  vcf9_operations_hcx_httpd:
    type: custom
    desc: The VMware Cloud Foundation Operations HCX Apache HTTP service must initiate session logging upon start up.
    control_id: VCFJ-9X-000008
    scored: true
    profile:
      - default
    information: |-
      Verify the "log_config_module" is present.

      At the command prompt, run the following:

      # httpd -M | grep -i "log_config_module"

      Example output:

      log_config_module (shared)

      If the "log_config_module" is not found, this is a finding.

      Verify the "CustomLog" directive is defined.

      At the command prompt, run the following:

      # grep -i "CustomLog" /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf /opt/vmware/config/apache-httpd/hcx-ssl.conf /opt/vmware/config/apache-httpd/hcx-virtual-hosts.conf

      Example output:

      CustomLog "/common/logs/httpd/access.log" common

      If "CustomLog" is not present, this is a finding.

      If "CustomLog" does not use a "LogFormat" with the required elements, this is a finding.

      Note: The required elements can be found in the "LogFormat" control VCFJ-9X-000007.
    rationale: |-
      An attacker can compromise a web server during the startup process. If logging is not initiated until all the web server processes are started, key information may be missed and not be available during a forensic investigation. To ensure all logable events are captured, the web server must begin logging once the first web server process is initiated.
    remediation: |-
      Navigate to and open:

      /etc/httpd/conf/httpd.conf

      Note: If the offending configuration was found in a different file edit that file instead.

      Add or update the "CustomLog" directive, for example:

      CustomLog "/common/logs/httpd/access.log" common

      Reload the configuration by running the following command:

      # systemctl reload httpd
